## ðŸ“Š FRIDAY 2.0 Backend â€” Files, Purpose & Technologies

| File / Module                       | Used For (One Line)                                                            | Technologies / Tools Used                     |
| ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- |
| `main.py`                           | Main execution loop coordinating input, intent processing, plugins, and output | Python, plugin architecture, state management |
| `core/state.py`                     | Stores global assistant state and short-term memory                            | Python globals, session state                 |
| `core/router.py`                    | Routes classified intents to the appropriate plugin                            | Python dictionaries, dynamic dispatch         |
| `core/plugin_base.py`               | Defines a common structure for all plugins                                     | Python OOP (inheritance, base classes)        |
| `core/intents.py`                   | Maintains a centralized list of supported intents                              | Python dictionaries                           |
| `core/confirmation.py`              | Handles user confirmation for sensitive actions                                | Stateful logic                                |
| `input/text.py`                     | Accepts text input when microphone is disabled or unavailable                  | Python standard input                         |
| `input/voice.py`                    | Converts spoken input to text offline                                          | Whisper, sounddevice, ffmpeg, NumPy, SciPy    |
| `output/console.py`                 | Displays assistant responses and forwards them to speech output                | Python print                                  |
| `output/speech.py`                  | Converts text responses to offline speech output                               | pyttsx3, threading, queue                     |
| `models/intent_model.py`            | Classifies user input into structured intents and entities                     | Ollama, prompt engineering, JSON, regex       |
| `models/ollama_client.py`           | Communicates with the local LLM for intent classification                      | Ollama (local LLM)                            |
| `plugins/system/open_app.py`        | Opens applications installed on the system                                     | PowerShell, Windows AppsFolder, subprocess    |
| `plugins/system/close_app.py`       | Closes running system applications                                             | taskkill, subprocess                          |
| `plugins/system/volume.py`          | Controls system audio volume                                                   | Windows audio APIs                            |
| `plugins/system/system_status.py`   | Retrieves system status information                                            | psutil, system APIs                           |
| `plugins/system/screenshot.py`      | Captures screenshots of the system                                             | PIL, OS-level screenshot tools                |
| `plugins/system/power.py`           | Performs power operations like shutdown or restart                             | OS power commands                             |
| `plugins/system/voice_toggle.py`    | Enables or disables microphone and speech output                               | Global state toggling                         |
| `plugins/productivity/notes.py`     | Manages creation, listing, and deletion of notes                               | SQLite, in-memory storage                     |
| `plugins/productivity/reminders.py` | Handles reminders and scheduling tasks                                         | SQLite, scheduling logic                      |
| `plugins/productivity/alarms.py`    | Creates and manages alarms                                                     | Time-based triggers                           |
| `plugins/Memory/memory_recall.py`   | Recalls short-term memory and past context                                     | State memory retrieval                        |

